comments: Poeltl (SAS) establishes himself in a screening position in Rondo's (LAL) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Davis (LAL) firms up in a screening position in Bates-Diop's (SAS) path and absorbs the contact.
Anthony (LAL) does not bring any part of his hand underneath the ball as he splits the defenders on his drive to the basket.
Poeltl (SAS) extends his arm out and marginal contact occurs as he brushes Anthony's (LAL) arm, which does not affect his ability to finish his driving shot attempt.
Monk (LAL) grabs the made basket and throws the ball to the referee, delaying the Spurs from inbounding the ball.
Poeltl (SAS) establishes himself in a screening position in Rondo's (LAL) path and absorbs the contact as Rondo goes over the pick.
Anthony (LAL) is in the paint for about three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Poeltl (SAS) does not extend his forearm into Anthony (LAL) and marginal contact occurs as he pursues the rebound.
Monk (LAL) legally contests Vassell's (SAS) jump shot attempt.
Poeltl (SAS) makes clean ball contact to tap the rebound away from Davis (LAL).
Poeltl (SAS) establishes himself in a screening position in Reaves' (LAL) path and absorbs the contact to his chest.
At the start of the drive, Reaves (LAL) briefly places a hand to Walker IV's (SAS) front and the contact is marginal as it does not affect his SQBR.
Poeltl (SAS) establishes himself in a screening position in Reaves' (LAL) path and marginal contact occurs to his side as he goes over the pick.
Davis (LAL) extends his arm out and makes clean ball contact during Walker IV's (SAS) pass attempt. Any follow-through contact after the deflection is deemed marginal.
Anthony (LAL) makes contact with Poeltl's (SAS) shoulder, which affects his shot near the rim.
Anthony (LAL) extends his forearm into and delivers contact to Murray's (SAS) back, which dislodges him into Davis (LAL) during the rebound.
Bates-Diop (SAS) maintains a legal guarding position on Davis (LAL) and cleanly deflects the pass away.
Anthony (LAL) legally contests Murray's (SAS) jump shot attempt.
Davis (LAL) makes clean ball contact to tap the rebound away from Poeltl (SAS).
Davis (LAL) establishes himself in a screening position in Bates-Diop's (SAS) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Poeltl (SAS) engages on the screen and marginal contact occurs as he disengages from Bazemore (LAL). Bazemore loses his balance  and incidental leg to leg contact occurs, which causes him to stumble.
Poeltl (SAS) jumps alongside of and absorbs the contact initiated by Bazemore (LAL) as he collapses his forearm in during the play at the basket.
Murray (SAS) makes hand on ball contact during his attempted block of Davis' (LAL) putback shot at the basket.
Vassell (SAS) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact during the driving shot attempt by Westbrook (LAL).
Davis (LAL) pulls up and absorbs any marginal contact initiated by Murray (SAS) during his driving shot attempt.
Murray (SAS) legally contests Davis' (LAL) jump shot attempt.
Bazemore (LAL) cleanly pokes the ball loose from Bates-Diop (SAS) as he dribbles up the court.
